The paper deals with the index coding problem, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper uses semidefinite programming (SDP), which is a common technique in optimization and algorithms research (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial analysis of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.NA). The use of SDP and graph theory in the paper suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI (social and information networks) and cs.CC (computational complexity).
